&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Small Talk …&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Martin Thoma</dc:creator><pubDate>Sat, 10 May 2014 02:04:00 +0200</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:martin-thoma.com,2014-05-10:/discussions-with-friends/</guid><category>Discussions</category><category>Friendship</category><category>Politics</category><category>Progress</category></item><item><title>How to apply the Viterbi algorithm</title><link>https://martin-thoma.com/apply-viterbi-algorithm/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;The goal of the Viterbi algorithm is find the most likely sequence of hidden states given some observed events.&lt;/p&gt;
